on-off grazing
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a form of rotational grazing [where stock are offered pasture or crop for only three to four hours each day and are fed on a wintering-pad or sacrifice paddock for the other twenty hours.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
